WellNest - Women’s Safety & Well-being Platform
WellNest is a dedicated digital ecosystem designed to empower women by providing a safe, supportive space for mental health support, legal awareness, and emergency resources. The platform features a unique dual-interface: a "Cyber-Noir" dark theme for administrative tasks and a soft, empathetic "Blush" theme for users.

🌟 Features
👩‍💻 User Portal (The Blush Suite)
Legal Awareness (Know Your Rights): An interactive grid of key Indian laws protecting women, with detailed modal pop-ups for each Act.

Virtual Counseling: A specialized booking system to schedule sessions with licensed professionals.

Video Consultations: Integrated video conferencing via Jitsi Meet for secure, private sessions.

Emergency Helplines: A mobile-responsive directory of Coimbatore-specific and National helplines for immediate assistance.

Feedback System: Post-meeting surveys to ensure service quality and user satisfaction.

🩺 Counsellor Portal
Slot Management: Tools for counsellors to create and manage their availability.

Booking Overview: A dashboard to view upcoming appointments and launch virtual meeting rooms.

🔐 Admin Portal (The Cyber-Noir Suite)
Counsellor Management: Securely add or remove licensed counsellors from the platform.

User Oversight: View and manage registered users to maintain platform integrity.

Secure Authentication: Role-based access control for Admins, Counsellors, and Users.

🎨 Design Philosophy
Admin/Counsellor Side: High-contrast Black & Neon Pink theme for a professional, focused, and "tech-forward" feel.

User Side: Inverted Blush White & Soft Pink theme to provide a calming, welcoming, and empathetic user experience.

Animations: Smooth transitions using CSS Keyframes (Fade-ins, Scale-pops, and Hover-glows) across the entire platform.

🛠️ Tech Stack
Frontend: HTML5, CSS3 (Modern Flexbox/Grid), JavaScript (ES6+).

Communication: EmailJS for automated booking confirmations.

Video: Jitsi Meet API for secure video conferencing.

Backend Support: Node.js/Express (Expected for full functionality) with a RESTful API structure.